Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.37,0:01:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.07,0:02:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you sell me something to eat?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.77,0:02:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Take a look at these rice paddies! \NThis summer has been too cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.90,0:02:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We've our hands full trying to gather \Nenough stock for ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.48,0:02:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Just give it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.46,0:02:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Go to the village past the next mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.28,0:02:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard that they're the only ones with \Na bountiful harvest this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.24,0:02:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, don't give him bad advice.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.32,0:02:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd better not go there. \NThe rice there is not normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.97,0:02:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,They get a bountiful harvest every time \Nwhen there's a disaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.54,0:02:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I hear it's a curse by their ancestors.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.73,0:02:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a "parting harvest".
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.05,0:02:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&HE6F1E5&}It's a "parting harvest."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.01,0:02:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Meaning, someone will be taken by our ancestors again.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.89,0:02:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Who will it be this year?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.61,0:02:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The ancestors choose from the weakest among us.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.91,0:02:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow. What impressive rice paddies!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.43,0:02:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are you? What do you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.43,0:03:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I was just wondering if you wouldn't mind selling me something to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.67,0:03:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't have anything to give to strangers.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.57,0:03:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't harvest enough every year.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.18,0:03:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We've to store our harvest when we can.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.63,0:03:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I see, then you're saying that this year's \Nbountiful harvest is a miracle?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.11,0:03:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.70,0:03:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Our ancestors watch over us \Nsince we always worship them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.28,0:03:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And in exchange, they take a life, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.76,0:03:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a pretty harsh thing for your ancestors to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.54,0:03:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't have... a choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.75,0:03:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't look like you really believe that...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.49,0:03:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you tell me what's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.56,0:03:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Every time a natural disaster occurs, the fields of this village produce a bountiful harvest.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.97,0:04:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I've heard it's been happening from very long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.72,0:04:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And, in such years, without fail, in the autumn,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.09,0:04:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,someone sprouts an auspicious tooth in their mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.18,0:04:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That tooth falls out at the end of autumn \Nand that person... {\alpha&HFF&}dies.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.32,0:04:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That tooth falls out at the end of autumn \Nand that person... dies.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.14,0:04:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been told through the generations that the life is an offering to the ancestors for the bountiful harvest.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.52,0:04:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, we all have been thankful for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.07,0:04:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Without these miracles,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.72,0:04:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,none of us would've been able to \Ncontinue living on this unfertile land.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.79,0:04:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Did those who lose their lives have anything in common?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.75,0:04:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It is said... the weakest go first.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.38,0:04:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Are the bodies buried?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.32,0:04:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.35,0:04:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What about the tooth?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.71,0:04:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The tooth is kept in the shrine by the head priest.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.29,0:05:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Head priest?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.36,0:05:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,He's the person who takes care of \Nall the religious services in this village.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.70,0:05:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll eventually take his place, \Nso he's teaching me various things.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.71,0:05:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's said that soon after the tooth falls out, \Nit's only visible to the head priest.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.54,0:05:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why the head priest is the one who keeps it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.86,0:05:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Why were you chosen to be his successor?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.67,0:05:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Because, like the head priest, sometimes I'm able to see things that others can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.00,0:05:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to meet your head priest.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.57,0:05:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Head priest!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.53,0:05:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if he's in the back fields.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.34,0:05:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Agricultural literature, and a journal...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.46,0:05:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not often that I've a visitor.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.41,0:05:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.03,0:05:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Just who are you, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.91,0:05:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I am a mushi-shi, Ginko.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.34,0:06:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm looking for something called the Narazu seed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.97,0:06:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.39,0:06:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Sane, aren't you in the middle of your fieldwork?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.24,0:06:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Come back when you're done.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.51,0:06:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,This year, we have a bountiful harvest.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.94,0:06:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We won't be able to catch up \Nunless we're well-prepared.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.12,0:06:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.36,0:06:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Are you still worried about your mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.36,0:06:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll be okay. She'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.43,0:06:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.97,0:06:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, let her eat this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.69,0:06:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.67,0:06:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I've heard that some mushi-shi came to these parts during the previous head priest's time, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.30,0:06:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But you're wasting your time. \NThere's no such seed here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.65,0:06:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're saying this good harvest is \Nbecause of your ancestors' grace?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.31,0:06:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Our ancestors' grace?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.99,0:06:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, that is a factor, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.21,0:07:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of everyone's faith, we're able to work without abandoning this village.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.07,0:07:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's not all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.24,0:07:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,For many years, we've all been \Nstudying ways to enrich the soil.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.37,0:07:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The result can be seen at times \Nwith harvests like this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.99,0:07:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Every year, our crops increase, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.33,0:07:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Then what about the auspicious tooth?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.01,0:07:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Adults can sprout a tooth on rare occasions.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.26,0:07:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It has nothing to do with the harvest.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.25,0:07:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Please be on your way now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.17,0:07:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,May I ask just one more question?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.09,0:07:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.47,0:07:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You seem to know about the Narazu seed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.48,0:07:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I've heard about it from the previous head priest.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.72,0:07:50.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a seed that a mushi-shi sealed a "light vein", \Nor something like that, into it, I think...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.74,0:07:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.41,0:07:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You probably can even intuitively \Nunderstand what a "light vein" is,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.82,0:07:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,because you seem to have the ability to see mushi...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.25,0:08:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The feebler the mushi is, the more light it takes on.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.71,0:08:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,That's because it's so similar to the Kouki,\Nwhich is the basis of mushi.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.01,0:08:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The light vein is the path in which the Kouki runs.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.62,0:08:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,In a sense, it is life itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.37,0:08:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,If you can manipulate it, it can be used for anything—
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.85,0:08:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,1389)} even immortality or resurrection.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.40,0:08:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, doing so is the biggest\N taboo among mushi-shi.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.29,0:08:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,However, there've been many cases of it happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.37,0:08:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,That seed is one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.51,0:08:35.39,Default,,0,0,0,,If you plant it in the ground, it'll bring a good\N harvest for that year in that area
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.39,0:08:39.49,Default,,0,0,0,,but in return, it'll take a life from among those that benefited from it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.58,0:08:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what we know of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.21,0:08:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And? What do you plan to do \Nwith that seed once you find?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.33,0:08:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you destroy it or would you use it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.57,0:08:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I was going to ask you that same question.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.03,0:08:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What would you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.41,0:09:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What if you obtained a seed that could save \Nmany lives at the cost of one life?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.76,0:09:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd probably use it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.48,0:09:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,If such a seed really does exist, it would be a sin not to use it and let people suffer.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.61,0:09:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,But, if that person planted the seed knowing that it'll cost one person's life—
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.64,0:09:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,it's the same as murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.19,0:09:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how many lives can be saved,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.33,0:09:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the person who dies is forced to be \Na sacrifice regardless of his or her will.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.40,0:09:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,If that's the cost of the sin,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.72,0:09:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,then anyone would dirty their hands...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.70,0:09:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,if it means saving two lives at the cost of one.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.18,0:09:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed, when you look at it from the short span of one year, it'd be senseless not to use it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.09,0:09:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,But once you use it, you'll keep using it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.69,0:09:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And, that seed is alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.71,0:09:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Each time you use it, more powerful the effect is.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.88,0:09:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually, it could become something \Nthat destroys the balance.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.09,0:09:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're saying you wouldn't use it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.74,0:10:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you afford... not to?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.24,0:10:05.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know. I've never lived in a village.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.87,0:10:08.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And I would leave that place \Nbefore it came to that point.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.09,0:10:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Here... in this land...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.35,0:10:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Our ancestor's flesh and blood sleep here!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.51,0:10:18.10,Default,,0,0,0,,They pioneered the land and made it what it's today.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.10,0:10:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That's our only pride!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.77,0:10:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't planting something abnormal in that ground mean you're violating the soil?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.58,0:10:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What am I saying? This is all supposition.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.52,0:10:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I know what you're saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.60,0:10:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,If there really is such a seed...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.87,0:10:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,935)}...I would think about it more carefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.48,0:10:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.86,0:10:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Such a seed is too much for one man to handle.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.85,0:11:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like an overabundant rice stalk hangs its head,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.16,0:11:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,that seed will certainly fall from \Nthat man's hands, onto the soil below...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.45,0:11:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,1768)}unaware of the suffering it'll cause \Nthe people in its aftermath.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.20,0:11:22.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! Are you done chatting already?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.38,0:11:25.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, pretty much.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.05,0:11:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And... will you save us all?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.83,0:11:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. But I first need to get \Nthe consent of the entire village...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.10,0:11:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,after I explain how the "parting harvest" works.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.70,0:11:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you have everyone gather somewhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.84,0:11:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,S-sure. But... just what are you planning to...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.65,0:11:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you suggesting we burn down the rice paddies...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.95,0:11:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,...because we've no choice but to destroy the seed before someone sprouts an auspicious tooth?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.29,0:11:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's right. So you're finally admitting the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.36,0:12:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got it wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.72,0:12:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if we do that, no one will be saved.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.28,0:12:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you trying to make everyone starve to death?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.41,0:12:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,All you've to do is live somewhere else for a year.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.39,0:12:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Once everyone lives separately, they can probably survive one way or other for a year.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.25,0:12:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,By spring, the ashes should have fertilized the soil.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.03,0:12:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,How many do you think will return \Nonce they leave this land?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.73,0:12:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,They're able to tolerate it because none of them know...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.53,0:12:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,what a real bountiful harvest is!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.39,0:12:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,This is how it should be...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.11,0:12:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't allow you to tell everyone such strange tales!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.81,0:12:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Head priest!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.49,0:12:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Does he have some kind of illness?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.38,0:12:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure, but he didn't seem well of late,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.87,0:12:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and I saw him taking medicine sometimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.84,0:13:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Medicine?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.33,0:13:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm pretty sure this contains it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.94,0:13:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure for what reason \Nyou've been taking this poison,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.15,0:13:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,but isn't it irresponsible to die \Nleaving things the way they're?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.90,0:13:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, mushi-shi...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.26,0:13:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Since you're suggesting we burn the rice paddies,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.34,0:13:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't seem like you came hoping to use that seed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.16,0:13:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Please... I've made the decision to be \Nthe last sacrifice for the seed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.87,0:13:51.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The one who is said to have brought \Nthe seed here in the first place,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.03,0:13:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,is the head priest before the previous one.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.02,0:14:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Thereafter, every time a natural disaster occurred, the seed was used,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.54,0:14:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,but in order to prevent panic, \Nonly the head priests knew the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.03,0:14:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It was 20 years ago when the first natural disaster occurred after I became the head priest,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.13,0:14:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'd to consider using the seed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.59,0:14:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I have to use it! If I don't...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.27,0:14:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm stepping out.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.38,0:14:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.81,0:14:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's for the best.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.76,0:14:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I was only thinking of the best \Ninterest of the entire village.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.16,0:14:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,718)\i1}It's... for the best.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.16,0:14:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So I was unaware that my wife was\N hiding her illness from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.05,0:14:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,In autumn, the one who sprouted \Nthe auspicious tooth was... my wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.59,0:15:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.98,0:15:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Have some rice,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.71,0:15:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,or you will die, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.13,0:15:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,933)}What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.66,0:15:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Please eat it even if it hurts.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.78,0:15:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,If you eat my life, I don't feel afraid of dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.94,0:15:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Despite it being the rice that it was,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.27,0:15:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,my body greedily accepted it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.17,0:15:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I was going to throw out the seed which had eventually fallen out of my wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.19,0:15:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But... I started to think about the next natural disaster, which was sure to come sooner or later.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.25,0:15:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,894)}Then I realized I could use the seed one more time without having to sacrifice someone's life.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.94,0:15:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,934)}Finally, this year,the time had come to use it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.78,0:16:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I plan to have Sane destroy the seed \Nthat falls out of my mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.63,0:16:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I hear it'll be destroyed if it's buried in the place that you call the path of the light vein.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.50,0:16:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But I don't plan to tell him about the seed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.33,0:16:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you really okay with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.33,0:16:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,More than anyone, you want to live here and see the future of this land, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.57,0:16:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I can see {\i1}it;{\i0} if we don't give up, \Nthis land will slowly become fertile.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.05,0:16:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Surely, the day should come someday \Nwhere we can live comfortably.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.74,0:16:59.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how many generations it'll take...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.45,0:17:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But either way, I won't be able to \Nsee it with my eyes anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.85,0:17:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. I'll let it play out as you wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.93,0:17:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But let me ask you one more thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.17,0:17:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Head priest!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.12,0:17:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,My mom... She's gonna be okay now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.59,0:17:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,She's eating and slowly getting better.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.13,0:17:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Really? That's good to hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.57,0:17:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you so.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.16,0:17:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.01,0:18:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, Sane. We need to talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.49,0:18:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,896)}It's really important. I want you to listen carefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.82,0:18:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Sane, the ritual prayer sounds \Ndifferent from last year's.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.44,0:18:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, no one has sprouted an auspicious tooth yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.33,0:18:21.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I haven't heard any news of it yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.85,0:18:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe this year's bountiful harvest \Nwasn't a "parting harvest."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.87,0:18:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Then that means that it's truly\N due to all our hard work...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.97,0:18:47.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.98,0:18:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The festival... is carrying on fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.57,0:18:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone is having fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.29,0:19:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.82,0:19:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll do exactly what you asked.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.73,0:19:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Head priest...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.41,0:19:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Why does it have to be this way?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.49,0:19:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,This isn't how it should be!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.00,0:19:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't tell anyone what I'm about to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.93,0:19:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me ask you one more thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.58,0:19:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you that the light vein is like life itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.02,0:20:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,but it can't revive a living being even if it was taken in.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.47,0:20:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But the one thing that can resuscitate life is that seed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.28,0:20:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a gamble but, even animals would be able to come back to life, if that seed is ingested.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.06,0:20:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Only, unlike vegetation, the light vein will probably continue to live within you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.10,0:20:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,If that happens, you'll become an immortal being...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.94,0:20:30.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you handle that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.51,0:20:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought doing that's the biggest\N taboo among mushi-shi.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.59,0:20:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you... get away with doing that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.97,0:20:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't say anything, no one will find out.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.70,0:20:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't even know if it'll work.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.93,0:20:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not even sure if it'll spell happiness for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.61,0:20:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you're willing to take a chance...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.73,0:20:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,This is my apology to you for wrangling out the\Ntruth about the seed from your wounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.76,0:20:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't mind dirtying my hands a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.33,0:21:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Give it a lot of thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.07,0:21:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have to think too hard to give you my answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.48,0:21:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to see it through after all...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.62,0:21:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,how this land will develop...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.06,0:21:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,...and whether what I've done up\N till now was right or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.12,0:21:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Thereafter, it's said that...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.37,0:21:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}the story of that year's bountiful harvest was forever talked about in that village.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.13,0:22:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}At the same time, a strange legend had also begun.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.54,0:22:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The rice harvested by that year's bountiful harvest,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.70,0:22:16.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}the first not to be a "parting harvest",\Nwas said to have resurrected a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.29,0:22:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The man became ageless and immortal, \Ntraveling around the country,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.84,0:22:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,2857)\i1}and at times returning to convey new farming methods to enrich the land.
